      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOO DARDY (5) comes here third-up and with some strong performances under his belt. On the quick turnaround today, but boasts a good third-up record and the splits he's run in his past couple suggests 1200m is ideal now. Looks the one to beat with improvement on the cards.  CHARINO (2) sat closer last start and was far too good, putting his rivals to the sword to win by 2.1L. This looks to set up perfectly for him yet again with Harvey replacing the apprentice hoop. Should get every chance to repeat the dose. YORGA PRIDE (7) disappointed on resumption but she is much better than she showed there. Winkers and the cross over nose band go on now and she can improve sharply with that run under her belt. THE CALABRESE (6) steps out to 1200m again today on the back of a couple strong efforts recently. Sure to be in the finish again. SUPERNATURAL (8) has trialled well and can return with a positive performance.",
